==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/藞b忙t蓹l藢伞ra蕣nd/}}
*{{SAMPA|/"b{t@l%graUnd/}}

===Etymology===
From [[battle]] + [[grounds]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A location where a [[battle]] may be fought, or has been fought.
#:''The farmer's field was a civil war '''battleground''', and relics such a minnie bullets were frequently found while plowing.''
# Figuratively, any subject of [[dispute]] or [[contention]].
#:''Abortion was becoming the season's big political '''battleground''', once again.''

